# Project Guide

## Identity
Solo developer. Planning/Design/Dev/Test/Ops/Marketing.

## Tech Stack
SvelteKit 5 / Firebase / TypeScript / Supabase / Cloudflare Pages / Tailwind CSS 4

## Principles
- **Plan first**: Use /brainstorming → /writing-plans (superpowers) before coding
- **TDD**: Tests before code (superpowers:test-driven-development)
- **SSOT (Single Source of Truth)**: Every piece of data lives in exactly ONE canonical location. All other consumers read from that source — never duplicate, never hardcode.
  - Config values → one config file or env var
  - Business rules → one module, re-exported where needed
  - UI strings → i18n files only
  - API URLs / endpoints → one constants file
  - Type definitions → one source, re-exported (no redeclaring the same shape)
- **Security**: No API key exposure, server-side processing
- **Cost**: Minimize unnecessary API calls and DB reads
- **No hardcoding**: Use i18n keys or constants

